Use the standard library
This is how to even_odd_palindrome of n:
   Remember that even is 0
   Remember that odd is 0
   Remember that i is 1
   Do this n times:
      Remember that s is tostring of i
      Remember that r is reverse of s
      When s is r, then:
         Remember that d is digits of i
         Remember that parity is remainder of d and 2
         When parity is 0, then:
            Increase even
         But, if not:
            Increase odd
         End when
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is [even, odd]
Now you know